<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Warning!</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Insane idea approaching.<br>
<br>
This is what I'd like to see come out of this, but I'm just dreaming here.<br>
<br>
You have 5 notes and 5 new words, plus the 5 different &quot;bindings&quot;.<br>
<br>
Let's say the final combine consist of 1 note + 1 word + binding + dropped parchment.  <br>
<br>
Now the type of binding would determine the spell type, such as Conjuration binding.  The parchment would determine the spell level.  And the combination of note + words would determine what <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>exact</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> spell results.  The 5x5 gives you 25 possible combinations in each of the 5 different types of spell categories.  So if this were true, you could eventually find a way to create a certain level 62 conjuration spell once the receipe was discovered.<br>
<br>
This would reduce the purely random rewards, but still use the parchments to gain a spell.<br>
